      • initialize

        public void initialize​(java.net.URL url,
                       java.util.ResourceBundle resourceBundle)
        I had a runtime error that made it so that when I would save, the partId would change but be in the correct position. For example, I would select "Part 3" and modify it, save it then it would liks it as "12" in the third position I worked with Professor Mark Kinkead on the issue but was unable to find the error until I realized that In one area the autoID didn't refactor to autoIndex (which is odd) so once I found that out, I changed it to autoIndex and everything worked!
        Specified by:
        initialize in interface javafx.fxml.Initializable
